14	MCS2E31	Advanced Computer Networks	1551	{}	Elective            	{"To give the students an understanding of the principles behind the latest advances in computer network technology, from IPv6 extending to pervasive and ubiquitous computing"}	[{"title": "Opportunistic and Social Networks", "topics": ["Handling Spectrum Scarcity and Disruption", "Architecture of Cognitive Radio Network (CRN) and Delay Tolerant Networks (DTN)", "Routing in Opportunistic Mobile and Social Networks", "Multicasting", "Single-node", "Multiple-copy", "and Single-copy model", "Interest-based Data Dissemination", "User Interest Profile", "Multi-party data transmission", "System Implementation", "Quality-of-Service (QoS)", "QoS parameters", "Metrics and classification", "Network QoS parameters (bandwidth", "delay", "etc.)", "System QoS parameters (reliability", "capacity", "etc.)", "Task QoS parameters (memory", "CPU usage", "response time", "etc.)", "Extension QoS parameters (reputation", "security", "etc.)"]}, {"title": "IoT Networks", "topics": ["Convergence of domains", "Key technologies for IoT and its components", "Multi-homing", "Sensing", "Actuation", "Data Aggregation", "IoT communication patterns", "IoT data and its impact on communication", "Characteristics of IoT networks", "Protocols for IoT", "NFC (Near field communication)", "Tactile Internet", "Caching", "Edge computing", "Inter-dependencies", "SoA", "Gateways", "Comparison between IoT and Web", "Complexity of IoT networks", "Scalability", "Protocol classification", "MQTT", "SMQTT", "CoAP", "XMPP", "AMQP", "Wireless HART protocol and layered architecture", "HART network manager", "HART vs ZigBee", "Cross layer QoS parameters"]}]	{"To understand the concepts behind Opportunistic, IoT and Software Defined Networking.","To identify different issues in Opportunistic, Social, IoT and SDN Networks.","To analyze various protocols proposed to handle issues related to Opportunistic, Social, IoT and SDN Networks."}	{"Jie Wu and Yunsheng Wang, Opportunistic Mobile Social Networks, CRC Press, 2015.","James F. Kurose and Keith W. Ross, Computer Networking: A Top-down Approach Featuring the Internet, Addison-Wesley, 2001.","Huitema, C., Routing in the Internet, 2nd ed., Prentice-Hall, 2000.","Peterson and Davie, Computer Networks: A Systems Approach, 5 th ed., Morgan Kaufmann, 2011.","Rajiv Ramaswami, Kumar N. Sivarajan, Galen H. Sasaki, Optical Networks: A Practical Perspective, Morgan Kaufmann.","Vijay Madisetti and Arshdeep Bahga, Internet of Things: A Hands-On- Approach, 2014, ISBN: 978 0996025515","Francis daCosta, Rethinking the Internet of Things: A Scalable Approach to Connecting Everything, 1 st Edition, Apress Publications, 2013."}	{}	{}	2025
15	MCS2E33	Intrusion Detection Systems	1551	{}	Elective            	{"The objective of this course is to provide an in depth introduction to the science and art of intrusion detection. The course covers methodologies, techniques, and tools for monitoring events in computer system or network, with the objective of preventing and detecting unwanted process activity and recovering from malicious behavior."}	[{"title": "Course Content", "topics": ["Overview of intrusions", "system intrusion process", "dangers of system intrusions", "history and state of the art of intrusion detection systems (IDSs): anomaly detection", "misuse detection", "types of IDS: Network-Based IDS. Host-Based IDS", "Hybrid IDS", "Intrusion Prevention Systems (IPS): Network-Based IPS", "Host-Based IPS", "Intrusion Detection Tools", "the limitations and open problems of intrusion detection systems", "advanced persistent threats", "case studies of intrusion detection systems against real-world threats and malware", "Statistical and machine approaches to detection of attacks on computers - Techniques for studying the Internet and estimating the number and severity of attacks", "network based attacks", "host based attacks. Statistical pattern recognition for detection and classification of attacks", "and techniques for visualizing network data", "etc"]}]	{"Obtain comprehensive knowledge on the subject of intrusion detection","Understand the state of the art of intrusion detection research","Get a hands-on exposure to the principles and techniques used in intrusion detection, as well as the technical challenges and fundamental limitations of intrusion detection become either a capable practitioner or independent researcher in intrusion detection."}	{"Roberto Di Pietro, Luigi V. Mancini, Intrusion Detection System, Springer, 2008.","Anderson, Ross (2001). Security Engineering: A Guide to Building Dependable Distributed Systems. New York: John Wiley & Sons. pp. 387–388. ISBN 978-0-471-38922-4.","Anderson, James P., \\"Computer Security Threat Monitoring and Surveillance,\\" Washing, PA, James P. Anderson Co., 1980."}	{}	{}	2025
16	MCS2E35	Distributed Computing	1551	{}	Elective            	{"To understand fundamental concepts of distributed computing and to acquire knowledge about development of fault tolerant protocols for middleware design."}	[{"title": "Unit 1: Design issues and challenges", "topics": ["Models and Architectures", "Synchronous Vs Asynchronous", "Classification of Failures in Distributed Systems", "Basic Techniques for Handling Time in Distributed Systems", "Physical Clocks", "Physical Clock Synchronization", "NTP", "Inter-process Communication", "Logical Clocks", "Scalar", "Vector", "and Matrix Clock", "Global State", "Consistent Snapshot Algorithms for FIFO", "Non-FIFO and Causal Delivery Systems", "Monitoring", "Consistency", "Necessary and Sufficient Condition for Consistent Snapshot", "Z-path and Z-cycles", "Synchronous Vs. Asynchronous Checkpointing and Recovery"]}, {"title": "Unit 2: Message Ordering and Group Communication Protocols", "topics": ["Naming in Distributed Systems", "Quiescence Detection", "Termination and Deadlock", "Weight-throwing", "MST-based", "and Message optimal Protocols", "Mutual Exclusion", "Shared Memory Vs. Message Passing Model", "2-P and n-P Algorithms", "Contention-based and Token-based algorithms", "Leader Election", "Election in Ring Networks", "Distributed Graph Algorithms for MST", "MIS", "CDS", "and other Virtual Structures"]}, {"title": "Unit 3", "topics": ["Agreement Protocols", "Coordinated Attack", "Distributed Consensus with Process Failures", "Synchronous Systems with Crash and Byzantine Failures", "Lower Bound", "EIG", "Phase-king Algorithm", "Concept of Valance", "FLP impossibility", "Wait-free and 1-failure Termination", "BGP", "Weak Byzantine Agreement", "k-agreement", "Approximate Agreement", "Distributed Commit", "2-PC and 3-PC protocols", "Distributed Scheduling and Load Balancing. Distributed File Systems", "and Distributed Shared Memory", "Security"]}]	{"Study software components of distributed computing systems. Know about the communication and interconnection architecture of multiple computer systems.","Recognize the inherent difficulties that arise due to distributed-ness of computing sources.","Understanding of networks & protocols, mobile & wireless computing and their applications to real world problems.","At the end students will be familiar with the design, implementation and issues of distributed system."}	{"Distributed Systems: Concepts and Design; G Colouris, J Dollimore, T Kindberg 3/e Pearson Ed. 2002.","Distributed Systems: Principles and Paradigm; Andrew S Tanenbaum, Maarten van Steen 3/e Pearson Ed.2002.","Principles of Distributed Systems, VK Garg, Kluwer Academic Publishers, 1996.","Distributed Systems and Algorithmic Approach by Su Kumar Boss, Chamal &Hall.","Principles of Distributed Computing by V K Garg, IEEE Press.","Distributed Computing by A D Kshem Kalyani & Mukesh Singha.","Distributed Algorithms by Nancy Lynch, Morgan Kaufmann Press.","Introduction to Distributed Algorithms by G Tel, Cambridge University."}	{}	{}	2025
17	MCS2E37	Biometric Security	1551	{}	Elective            	{"To provide students with understanding of biometrics, biometric equipment and standards applied to security."}	[{"title": "Overview of Biometrics", "topics": ["Definitions", "biometric modalities", "basic applications", "access control", "security"]}, {"title": "Biometric System Architecture", "topics": ["Scanning/digitizing", "enhancement", "feature extraction", "classification", "matching", "searching and verification"]}, {"title": "Biometric System Security", "topics": ["Biometric attacks/tampering", "solutions", "biometric encryption"]}]	{"Explain different biometrics parameters","Evaluate and design security systems incorporating biometrics","Perform R&D on biometrics methods and systems","Understand the privacy challenges of Biometrics","Explain the errors generated in biometric measurements","Understand the technology of biometrics for public policy matters involving security and privacy."}	{"Benjamin Muller, Security, Risk and the Biometric State: Governing Borders and Bodies, 1st Edition, Routledge, 2010.","Anil K Jain, Patrick Flynn, Arun A. (Eds.), Handbook of Biometrics, Springer, 2008.","Julian D. M. Ashbourn, Biometrics: Advanced Identify Verification: The Complete Guide, Springer-Verlag, 2000.","Davide Maltoni, Handbook of Fingerprint Recognition.","Biometric Systems: Technology, Design and Performance Evaluation, Editors: J. Wayman, A. Jain, D. Maltoni and D. Maio, Springer, 2005."}	{}	{}	2025
