43	MCS1E01	Data Warehousing and Data Mining	1551	{}	Elective            	{"Understand the principles and application of data mining and warehousing and also able to identify the scope and necessity of system.","Describe the theoretical constructs and processes of data mining and warehousing.","Investigate the various data mining and warehousing models and techniques, in solving the real world problems.","Design and analyze a lightweight prototype or simulation that supports the concept of data mining and warehousing."}	[{"title": "Data Warehousing and Business Analysis", "topics": ["Data warehousing Components \\u2013Building a Data warehouse \\u2013Data Warehouse Architecture \\u2013 DBMS Schemas for Decision Support \\u2013 Data Extraction", "Cleanup", "and Transformation Tools \\u2013Metadata \\u2013 reporting \\u2013 Query tools and Applications \\u2013 Online Analytical Processing (OLAP) \\u2013 OLAP and Multidimensional Data Analysis"]}, {"title": "Data Mining", "topics": ["- Data Mining Functionalities \\u2013 Data Preprocessing \\u2013 Data Cleaning \\u2013 Data Integration and Transformation \\u2013 Data Reduction \\u2013 Data Discretization and Concept Hierarchy Generation- Architecture of A Typical Data Mining Systems: Classification of Data Mining Systems. Association Rule Mining: - Efficient and Scalable Frequent Item set Mining Methods \\u2013 Mining Various Kinds of Association Rules \\u2013 Association Mining to Correlation Analysis \\u2013 Constraint-Based Association Mining"]}, {"title": "Classification and Prediction", "topics": ["- Issues Regarding Classification and Prediction \\u2013 Classification by Decision Tree Introduction \\u2013 Bayesian Classification \\u2013 Rule Based Classification \\u2013 Classification by Back propagation \\u2013 Support Vector Machines \\u2013 Associative Classification \\u2013 Lazy Learners \\u2013 Other Classification Methods \\u2013 Prediction \\u2013 Accuracy and Error Measures \\u2013 Evaluating the Accuracy of a Classifier or Predictor \\u2013 Ensemble Methods \\u2013 Model Section"]}, {"title": "Cluster Analysis", "topics": ["- Types of Data in Cluster Analysis \\u2013 A Categorization of Major Clustering Methods \\u2013 Partitioning Methods \\u2013 Hierarchical methods \\u2013 Density-Based Methods \\u2013 Grid-Based Methods \\u2013 Model-Based Clustering Methods \\u2013 Clustering High-Dimensional Data \\u2013 Constraint Based Cluster Analysis \\u2013 Outlier Analysis"]}, {"title": "Mining Object, Spatial, Multimedia, Text and Web Data", "topics": ["Multidimensional Analysis and Descriptive Mining of Complex Data Objects \\u2013 Spatial Data Mining \\u2013 Multimedia Data Mining \\u2013 Text Mining \\u2013 Mining the World Wide Web"]}]	{"To analyze the different issues in data mining and data warehousing.","To identify and understand various applications of data mining in real world.","To learn the various classification algorithms and analyze their performance."}	{"Han J, Pei J, Kamber M. Data Mining: concepts and techniques. 2011.","Berson A, Smith SJ. Data warehousing, data mining, and OLAP. McGraw-Hill. 1997.","Chen Z. Intelligent Data Warehousing: From data preparation to data mining. 2001."}	{}	{}	2025
44	MCS1E03	Software Architecture and Design Patterns	1551	{}	Elective            	{"To understand the fundamentals of software architecture.","To learn the various software architecture design components.","To understand the concept of patterns and catalog.","To learn about specific design patterns."}	[{"title": "Introduction to software architecture", "topics": ["Nature of software", "defining software", "software application domain. Architecture business cycle", "Defining software architecture", "Importance of software architecture", "Architectural patterns", "Reference models", "Reference architectures", "Architectural structures and views. Creating architecture quality attributes", "achieving qualities", "Architectural design and patterns", "designing the architecture", "Reconstructing software architecture"]}, {"title": "Analysis of architectures", "topics": ["Architecture evaluation", "Architecture design decision making", "ATAM", "CBAM. Moving from one system to many software product lines", "Building systems from off the shelf components", "Software architecture in future"]}, {"title": "Introduction to design patterns", "topics": ["Describing a design pattern", "design patterns in Smalltalk MVC. Catalog of design patterns", "Organizing the catalog", "role in solving design patterns", "Specifying object interfaces and implementations. Selection of design pattern", "Usage of design pattern"]}, {"title": "Discussing various design patterns", "topics": ["Creational patterns: Abstract factory", "Builder", "Factory method", "Prototype", "Singleton. Structural patterns: Bridge", "Composite", "Decorator", "Fa\\u00e7ade", "Flyweight", "Proxy. Behavioral patterns: Chain of responsibility", "Command", "Interpreter", "Iterator", "Mediator", "Memento", "Observer", "State", "Strategy", "Template method", "Visitor"]}, {"title": "A Case study", "topics": ["Design problems", "Document structure", "Formatting", "Embellishing the user interface", "Supporting the multiple window systems and multiple look-and-feel standards", "User operations", "Spelling checking and hyphenation. Case studies: A-7E \\u2013 A case study in utilizing architectural structures", "The World Wide Web \\u2013 a case study in interoperability", "Air traffic control \\u2013 a case study in designing for high availability"]}]	{"Learn and evaluate existing software architectures.","Develop software applications starting from software architecture and design.","Architect and design using architectural styles and design patterns."}	{"Richard N. Taylor, Nenad Medvidovic, and Eric M. Dashofy. Software architecture: foundations, theory, and practice. John Wiley & Sons, 2007.","Erich Gamma, John Vlissides, Ralph Johnson, Richard Helm. Design Patterns : Elements of Reusable Object-Oriented Software. Pearson, 2015","Bass L, Clements P, Kazman R. Software architecture in practice. Addison-Wesley Professional; 2003."}	{}	{}	2025
1	MCS2C01	Advanced Data Structures and Algorithms	1551	{}	Core                	{"To develop the understanding of advanced algorithms.","To study complexity of advanced algorithms.","Design new algorithms or modify existing ones for new applications and able to analyze the space & time efficiency of most algorithms."}	[{"title": "Data Structures", "topics": ["AVL trees", "Red black trees", "Balanced Multi-way trees", "Splay trees", "tries", "Segment trees", "Binomial heap and Fibonacci heap"]}, {"title": "Approximation Algorithms", "topics": ["Coping with NP-Hardness", "Greedy Approximation Algorithms", "Dynamic Programming and Weakly Polynomial-Time Algorithms", "Linear Programming Relaxations", "Randomized Rounding", "Vertex Cover", "set cover", "TSP", "knapsack", "bin packing", "subset-sum problem", "Load balancing", "Analysis of the expected time complexity of the algorithms"]}, {"title": "Randomized and Probabilistic Algorithms", "topics": ["Game-theoretic techniques", "Moments and Deviations", "Numerical Probabilistic algorithms", "Lovasz local lemma", "Markov Chains and Random Walks", "Algebraic Techniques", "Geometric Algorithms", "Randomized Quick sort", "Las Vegas and Monte Carlo algorithms", "Applications problems like load balancing", "packet routing etc"]}]	{"Apply basic concepts of approximation, randomization and distributed computing in algorithmic context.","Designs randomized parallel algorithms, approximation and distributed algorithms that run fast or that return the correct output with high probability.","Derives good upper bounds for the expected running time of advanced algorithms.","Can apply the probabilistic method to show the existence of certain combinatorial objects design and analyse."}	{"Introduction to Algorithms by Thomas H. Cormen, Charles E. Leiserson, Ronald L. Rivest and Clifford Stein. Third Edition. MIT Press and PHI, 2010.","Algorithm Design and Applications by Michael T. Goodrich and Roberto Tamassia, John wiley publication.",