75	DSPC 200	Data Mining and Analytics	1551	{}	Core                	{"The course explores the concepts and techniques of data mining, a promising and flourishing frontier in data science. Analyzing large amounts of data has become a necessity and the problem therefore arises as to “how to analyze the data”.","Data Mining is the subject dealing automated extraction of useful information or patterns representing knowledge implicitly stored in large databases, data warehouses, and other massive data repositories. It is a technology that blends traditional data analysis methods with sophisticated algorithms for association rule mining, clustering, classification and outlier analysis.","The course is designed to provide students with a broad understanding in the design and use of data mining algorithms.","The course will provide algorithmic as well as application perspectives of data mining."}	[{"title": "Unit-1: Data Mining and Data Pre-processing: Introduction to Data Mining", "topics": ["Motivation behind Data Mining", "Data Mining Tasks", "Issues in Data Mining Applications. Types of data", "Data Quality", "Data pre processing", "Similarity and Dissimilarity", "Outlier Analysis"]}, {"title": "Unit-2", "topics": ["Clustering: Introduction", "Applications", "K-Means Algorithm", "Hierarchical Algorithms", "Density based Algorithms", "Fuzzy c-Mean Algorithm", "Silhouette Coefficient", "DB-Index"]}, {"title": "Unit-3: Association Rule Mining: Introduction", "topics": ["Applications", "Market-Basket Analysis", "Frequent Itemsets", "Apriori Algorithm", "Alternative Methods", "FP Growth algorithm"]}, {"title": "Unit-4: Dimension Reduction and Introduction to Analytics: Feature Selection Techniques", "topics": ["Principal Component Analysis", "Classification overview"]}, {"title": "Unit-5: Web Data Mining: Social Network Analysis: Preliminaries and Properties", "topics": ["Homophily", "Triadic Closure", "Clustering Coefficient", "Centrality", "Community Detection in Graphs and Networks"]}]	{}	{"T1. Tan,Pang-Ning & others. “Introduction to Data Mining”Pearson Education, 2006.","Han J &Kamber M, “Data Mining: Concepts and Techniques,” Morgan Kaufmann Publishers, Second Edition, 2006","Christopher Bishop: “Pattern Recognition and Machine Learning”, Springer International Edition","Tom M. Mitchell: “Machine Learning”, The McGraw-Hill Companies, Inc.","Charu C. Aggarwal “Outlier Analysis” Springer International Publishing (2017)","Christopher D.M., Prabhakar R. &Hinrich S. “Introduction to Information Retrieval” Cambridge UP Online edition, 2009"}	{}	{}	2025
