110	CSPE 212	Competitive Programming and Efficient Coding for Problem Solving	1551	{}	Elective            	{"Identifying multiple alternate coding solutions of problems discussed in programming tests and Competitive Problems (CP) and developing understanding of their efficiency issues.","Designing and developing brute-force solutions followed by time/space efficient solutions for CP problems.","Learning commonly used problem solving approaches and applying them for coding the solutions for new problems."}	[{"title": "Unit 1: Overview of Efficient Coding for Problem Solving and CP: Introduction to competitive programming (CP); revisit of complexity analysis; introduction to online platforms such as codechef", "topics": ["codeforces etc and online submission", "constraints during CP", "online testing process and common errors such as TLE", "use of STL"]}, {"title": "Unit 2: Use of Number Theory for problem-solving: reducing time/space complexity of brute force coding solution of Sieve Method", "topics": ["Inverse Module", "Euclidian Method of factorization", "efficient coding for Permutation Combination", "XORing based and pattern-based solutions"]}, {"title": "Unit 3: Coding for Optimizing time and Space using Sequential Storage: two pointer approach; problem-solving using arrays and strings such as rotation on sorted arrays", "topics": ["duplicate removal", "string matching algorithms", "Kadane\\u2019s algo", "stacks", "priority-queues and hashing based efficient coding", "median based problems and alternate solutions"]}, {"title": "Unit 4: Applying Non-Linear Data Structures for real-life problems: design of efficient solutions for problems such as finding loops in a linked list", "topics": ["memory efficient DLL", "block reversal in LL", "problem solving using trees and binary trees", "Catalan numbers", "applications of graphs", "spanning tree and path algos for CP problems with reduced time/space complexity"]}, {"title": "Unit 5: CP Problem Solving using Advanced