91	estate-and-construction	58699	{}	{""}	{58705}	\N	\N	{"The Office of the Dean Students’ Welfare congratulates and warmly welcomes the batch of 2025 at the National Institute of Technology Kurukshetra. It gives us immense pleasure to inform you that the office is committed to working for the welfare of students at various levels. Taking cognizance of social, economic, and cultural diversities, we strive to render all facilities that allow young entrants to remain enthusiastic and motivated to demonstrate their skills and talents. The holistic development of students is our prime motive.","The Office of the Dean Students’ Welfare ensures the overall growth of students by providing ample opportunities and a platform to showcase and chisel their personality traits. We believe in maintaining a balance between academic and extracurricular activities, as the aim of education is not only to support academic excellence but also to promote all-round development of an individual. Holistic personality development involves the growth of intellectual, psychological, physical, emotional, and social skills to help individuals meet life’s demands and challenges, which are critical for success at both personal and professional fronts. Accordingly, the Institute has meticulously designed innovative techniques, activities, and workshops to foster balanced personality development.","Our focus is to promote value-based education because “Education without morals is like a ship without a compass, merely wandering nowhere” (Martin Luther King Jr.). Students are involved in a variety of activities including sports, literary, cultural, and managerial responsibilities such as the management and functioning of hostels, which encourage leadership skills and sensitivity toward the needs of different stakeholders. A Student Council actively promotes student participation in maintaining discipline and sharing ideas, interests, and concerns, thereby fostering a culture of cooperation, fraternity, assimilation, accommodation, and unity among students, contributing to the strengthening of the social fabric of the nation.","We are proud to inform you that the campus of the Institute is ragging-free. The Institute follows a strict policy of zero tolerance towards ragging, substance abuse, eve teasing, or any other criminal activity. Students are strictly warned to refrain from such activities, and any person found guilty will be subjected to strict disciplinary action as per law. Physical violence or any other form of abusive behavior towards fellow residents will not be tolerated within or outside the Institute premises. Anyone found guilty will be liable for strict disciplinary action, including suspension or rustication, depending on the severity of the case. Public display of affection is strictly prohibited.","We hope this handbook provides all necessary information about the Institute. The principal objective of this office is to extend all possible support for the growth and progress of students. The Office of the Dean (Students’ Welfare) is always open to students, and we invite suggestions for improvement. We wish you a very happy, healthy, and comfortable stay on the campus."}	{}
89	planning-and-development	58699	{}	{"Planning the expansion and diversification of institutional activities and preparation of all developmental proposals, the extent up to the submission of plan & estimates related to Civil, Electrical, Works, Sanitary, Network Systems, etc.","Maintenance of all necessary statistical data regarding plans & projects required for compilation of various reports periodically required to be sent to the Ministry of Human Resource Development and other agencies.","Monitoring the physical targets and utilization of funds in respect of Projects & Consultancy and in the preparation of relevant papers for submission of progress reports.","Formulating proposals for new courses and organizing meetings of faculty members and external experts for this purpose in this regard.","In the efforts to expand and monitor the activities of consultancy, testing, and sponsored research of the Institute and to ensure submission of progress reports.","In coordinating the formulation and conduct of non-formal and continuing education and extension programmes.","To manage the agenda and organization of the meeting for procurement of equipment related to projects, testing, and consultancy.","Providing necessary data for the budget and new estimates & plans to the Building & Works Committee to the Registrar."}	{58730}	\N	\N	{"The Office of the Dean Students’ Welfare congratulates and warmly welcomes the batch of 2025 at the National Institute of Technology Kurukshetra. It gives us immense pleasure to inform you that the office is committed to working for the welfare of students at various levels. Taking cognizance of social, economic, and cultural diversities, we strive to render all facilities that allow young entrants to remain enthusiastic and motivated to demonstrate their skills and talents. The holistic development of students is our prime motive.","The Office of the Dean Students’ Welfare ensures the overall growth of students by providing ample opportunities and a platform to showcase and chisel their personality traits. We believe in maintaining a balance between academic and extracurricular activities, as the aim of education is not only to support academic excellence but also to promote all-round development of an individual. Holistic personality development involves the growth of intellectual, psychological, physical, emotional, and social skills to help individuals meet life’s demands and challenges, which are critical for success at both personal and professional fronts. Accordingly, the Institute has meticulously designed innovative techniques, activities, and workshops to foster balanced personality development.","Our focus is to promote value-based education because “Education without morals is like a ship without a compass, merely wandering nowhere” (Martin Luther King Jr.). Students are involved in a variety of activities including sports, literary, cultural, and managerial responsibilities such as the management and functioning of hostels, which encourage leadership skills and sensitivity toward the needs of different stakeholders. A Student Council actively promotes student participation in maintaining discipline and sharing ideas, interests, and concerns, thereby fostering a culture of cooperation, fraternity, assimilation, accommodation, and unity among students, contributing to the strengthening of the social fabric of the nation.","We are proud to inform you that the campus of the Institute is ragging-free. The Institute follows a strict policy of zero tolerance towards ragging, substance abuse, eve teasing, or any other criminal activity. Students are strictly warned to refrain from such activities, and any person found guilty will be subjected to strict disciplinary action as per law. Physical violence or any other form of abusive behavior towards fellow residents will not be tolerated within or outside the Institute premises. Anyone found guilty will be liable for strict disciplinary action, including suspension or rustication, depending on the severity of the case. Public display of affection is strictly prohibited.","We hope this handbook provides all necessary information about the Institute. The principal objective of this office is to extend all possible support for the growth and progress of students. The Office of the Dean (Students’ Welfare) is always open to students, and we invite suggestions for improvement. We wish you a very happy, healthy, and comfortable stay on the campus."}	{}
86	student-welfare	58700	{}	{"He/she will advise the Director in organising students’ counselling.","He/she will be responsible for the publication of students’ magazines, newsletters, and similar publications.","He/she will advise the Director in matters related to students’ discipline and welfare.","He/she will assist the Director in matters related to the Students’ Union, Association, or Council.","He/she will coordinate the NCC, NSS, Games, Swimming Pool, Sports, Cultural, Co-curricular, and Extra-curricular activities of the students.","He/she will maintain records of alumni and correspond with them.","He/she will conduct inquiries into cases of student indiscipline.","He/she will correspond with parents or guardians of students regarding their progress and individual problems or welfare."}	{58739,58721}	deansw@nitkkr.ac.in	1744233448	{"The Office of the Dean Students’ Welfare congratulates and warmly welcomes the batch of 2025 at the National Institute of Technology Kurukshetra. It gives us immense pleasure to inform you that the office is committed to working for the welfare of students at various levels. Taking cognizance of social, economic, and cultural diversities, we strive to render all facilities that allow young entrants to remain enthusiastic and motivated to demonstrate their skills and talents. The holistic development of students is our prime motive.","The Office of the Dean Students’ Welfare ensures the overall growth of students by providing ample opportunities and a platform to showcase and chisel their personality traits. We believe in maintaining a balance between academic and extracurricular activities, as the aim of education is not only to support academic excellence but also to promote all-round development of an individual. Holistic personality development involves the growth of intellectual, psychological, physical, emotional, and social skills to help individuals meet life’s demands and challenges, which are critical for success at both personal and professional fronts. Accordingly, the Institute has meticulously designed innovative techniques, activities, and workshops to foster balanced personality development.","Our focus is to promote value-based education because “Education without morals is like a ship without a compass, merely wandering nowhere” (Martin Luther King Jr.). Students are involved in a variety of activities including sports, literary, cultural, and managerial responsibilities such as the management and functioning of hostels, which encourage leadership skills and sensitivity toward the needs of different stakeholders. A Student Council actively promotes student participation in maintaining discipline and sharing ideas, interests, and concerns, thereby fostering a culture of cooperation, fraternity, assimilation, accommodation, and unity among students, contributing to the strengthening of the social fabric of the nation.","We are proud to inform you that the campus of the Institute is ragging-free. The Institute follows a strict policy of zero tolerance towards ragging, substance abuse, eve teasing, or any other criminal activity. Students are strictly warned to refrain from such activities, and any person found guilty will be subjected to strict disciplinary action as per law. Physical violence or any other form of abusive behavior towards fellow residents will not be tolerated within or outside the Institute premises. Anyone found guilty will be liable for strict disciplinary action, including suspension or rustication, depending on the severity of the case. Public display of affection is strictly prohibited.","We hope this handbook provides all necessary information about the Institute. The principal objective of this office is to extend all possible support for the growth and progress of students. The Office of the Dean (Students’ Welfare) is always open to students, and we invite suggestions for improvement. We wish you a very happy, healthy, and comfortable stay on the campus."}	{58706,58810,58797}
88	faculty-welfare	58698	{}	{"Deputation of faculty to various institutions under Quality Improvement Programme under rules applicable to them.","He/she will advise the Director for deputation of the faculty members to various conferences, seminars, short-term courses, training programmes, foreign teaching/training assignments, etc.","He/she will chair the committee meetings for the evaluation of papers submitted or to be submitted to conferences/seminars by the faculty members.","He/she will assist the Director in organizing training programmes for faculty.","He/she will assist the Director in the supervision of the construction and maintenance work of buildings, roads, water supply, sanitation, lawns and gardens, communication networks, water coolers, air conditioners, telephones, etc.","He/she will assist the Director in maintaining discipline and work ethos among the various departments and faculty members.","He/she will assist the Director in maintaining high academic standards and achieving academic excellence in the institution.","Supervision over faculty discipline, integrity, and commitment."}	{}	\N	\N	{"The Office of the Dean Students’ Welfare congratulates and warmly welcomes the batch of 2025 at the National Institute of Technology Kurukshetra. It gives us immense pleasure to inform you that the office is committed to working for the welfare of students at various levels. Taking cognizance of social, economic, and cultural diversities, we strive to render all facilities that allow young entrants to remain enthusiastic and motivated to demonstrate their skills and talents. The holistic development of students is our prime motive.","The Office of the Dean Students’ Welfare ensures the overall growth of students by providing ample opportunities and a platform to showcase and chisel their personality traits. We believe in maintaining a balance between academic and extracurricular activities, as the aim of education is not only to support academic excellence but also to promote all-round development of an individual. Holistic personality development involves the growth of intellectual, psychological, physical, emotional, and social skills to help individuals meet life’s demands and challenges, which are critical for success at both personal and professional fronts. Accordingly, the Institute has meticulously designed innovative techniques, activities, and workshops to foster balanced personality development.","Our focus is to promote value-based education because “Education without morals is like a ship without a compass, merely wandering nowhere” (Martin Luther King Jr.). Students are involved in a variety of activities including sports, literary, cultural, and managerial responsibilities such as the management and functioning of hostels, which encourage leadership skills and sensitivity toward the needs of different stakeholders. A Student Council actively promotes student participation in maintaining discipline and sharing ideas, interests, and concerns, thereby fostering a culture of cooperation, fraternity, assimilation, accommodation, and unity among students, contributing to the strengthening of the social fabric of the nation.","We are proud to inform you that the campus of the Institute is ragging-free. The Institute follows a strict policy of zero tolerance towards ragging, substance abuse, eve teasing, or any other criminal activity. Students are strictly warned to refrain from such activities, and any person found guilty will be subjected to strict disciplinary action as per law. Physical violence or any other form of abusive behavior towards fellow residents will not be tolerated within or outside the Institute premises. Anyone found guilty will be liable for strict disciplinary action, including suspension or rustication, depending on the severity of the case. Public display of affection is strictly prohibited.","We hope this handbook provides all necessary information about the Institute. The principal objective of this office is to extend all possible support for the growth and progress of students. The Office of the Dean (Students’ Welfare) is always open to students, and we invite suggestions for improvement. We wish you a very happy, healthy, and comfortable stay on the campus."}	{}
90	research-and-consultancy	58724	{}	{"Frame rules for industrially sponsored research and consultancy.","Create and maintain a database regarding faculty expertise.","Facilitate through his/her office faculty in procuring equipment necessary to conduct research and consultancy work, recruitment of project staff.","Coordinate co-curricular activities (technical festivals, quizzes, etc.) for the students.","Provide guidance for submitting proposals to funding agencies such as Department of Science and Technology (DST), Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC), Board of Research in Nuclear Sciences (BRNS), Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO), Defense Research and Development Organisation (DRDO), Aeronautics Research and Development Board (AR&DB), Ministry of Information Technology, etc."}	{58747}	\N	\N	{"The Office of the Dean Students’ Welfare congratulates and warmly welcomes the batch of 2025 at the National Institute of Technology Kurukshetra. It gives us immense pleasure to inform you that the office is committed to working for the welfare of students at various levels. Taking cognizance of social, economic, and cultural diversities, we strive to render all facilities that allow young entrants to remain enthusiastic and motivated to demonstrate their skills and talents. The holistic development of students is our prime motive.","The Office of the Dean Students’ Welfare ensures the overall growth of students by providing ample opportunities and a platform to showcase and chisel their personality traits. We believe in maintaining a balance between academic and extracurricular activities, as the aim of education is not only to support academic excellence but also to promote all-round development of an individual. Holistic personality development involves the growth of intellectual, psychological, physical, emotional, and social skills to help individuals meet life’s demands and challenges, which are critical for success at both personal and professional fronts. Accordingly, the Institute has meticulously designed innovative techniques, activities, and workshops to foster balanced personality development.","Our focus is to promote value-based education because “Education without morals is like a ship without a compass, merely wandering nowhere” (Martin Luther King Jr.). Students are involved in a variety of activities including sports, literary, cultural, and managerial responsibilities such as the management and functioning of hostels, which encourage leadership skills and sensitivity toward the needs of different stakeholders. A Student Council actively promotes student participation in maintaining discipline and sharing ideas, interests, and concerns, thereby fostering a culture of cooperation, fraternity, assimilation, accommodation, and unity among students, contributing to the strengthening of the social fabric of the nation.","We are proud to inform you that the campus of the Institute is ragging-free. The Institute follows a strict policy of zero tolerance towards ragging, substance abuse, eve teasing, or any other criminal activity. Students are strictly warned to refrain from such activities, and any person found guilty will be subjected to strict disciplinary action as per law. Physical violence or any other form of abusive behavior towards fellow residents will not be tolerated within or outside the Institute premises. Anyone found guilty will be liable for strict disciplinary action, including suspension or rustication, depending on the severity of the case. Public display of affection is strictly prohibited.","We hope this handbook provides all necessary information about the Institute. The principal objective of this office is to extend all possible support for the growth and progress of students. The Office of the Dean (Students’ Welfare) is always open to students, and we invite suggestions for improvement. We wish you a very happy, healthy, and comfortable stay on the campus."}	{}
87	academic	58765	{}	{"Admission and enrolment of students","Finalization of Academic calendar, time-tables, registration of students for course work and examinations, classroom arrangements and all other requirements for proper conduct of class work.","Conduct of class tests and co-coordinating the finalization of session’s evaluations and for ensuring the timely declaration of results.","Supervision of the maintenance of up-to-date academic records of all categories of students.","Publication and distribution of the syllabi.","Organizing meetings of all the Institute level academic bodies.","Arranging the issue of all academic certificates, medals and prizes to the students.","To arrange for the conduct of those examinations which are to be conducted by the Institute as stipulated in the Institute regulations.","To formulate policies for the conduct of research and steps (0 maintain suitable stanidard by implementing the Board of Governors/Senate decision.","To execute the policy of the Senate in the conduct of P.G., PhD and other research programmes including the examination of the thesis.","To coordinate the conduct of the convocation.","All proposals to modify the teaching programmes will be considered by BOAC, for which Dean (Academic) ie. the Chairman and if approved will be sent to the Senate for formal approval.","To admit sponsored Early Faculty Induction Programme and Quality Improvement Programme candidates.","To suggest the Director take suitable steps from time to time to strive for high academic standards."}	{58822}	\N	\N	{"The Office of the Dean Students’ Welfare congratulates and warmly welcomes the batch of 2025 at the National Institute of Technology Kurukshetra. It gives us immense pleasure to inform you that the office is committed to working for the welfare of students at various levels. Taking cognizance of social, economic, and cultural diversities, we strive to render all facilities that allow young entrants to remain enthusiastic and motivated to demonstrate their skills and talents. The holistic development of students is our prime motive.","The Office of the Dean Students’ Welfare ensures the overall growth of students by providing ample opportunities and a platform to showcase and chisel their personality traits. We believe in maintaining a balance between academic and extracurricular activities, as the aim of education is not only to support academic excellence but also to promote all-round development of an individual. Holistic personality development involves the growth of intellectual, psychological, physical, emotional, and social skills to help individuals meet life’s demands and challenges, which are critical for success at both personal and professional fronts. Accordingly, the Institute has meticulously designed innovative techniques, activities, and workshops to foster balanced personality development.","Our focus is to promote value-based education because “Education without morals is like a ship without a compass, merely wandering nowhere” (Martin Luther King Jr.). Students are involved in a variety of activities including sports, literary, cultural, and managerial responsibilities such as the management and functioning of hostels, which encourage leadership skills and sensitivity toward the needs of different stakeholders. A Student Council actively promotes student participation in maintaining discipline and sharing ideas, interests, and concerns, thereby fostering a culture of cooperation, fraternity, assimilation, accommodation, and unity among students, contributing to the strengthening of the social fabric of the nation.","We are proud to inform you that the campus of the Institute is ragging-free. The Institute follows a strict policy of zero tolerance towards ragging, substance abuse, eve teasing, or any other criminal activity. Students are strictly warned to refrain from such activities, and any person found guilty will be subjected to strict disciplinary action as per law. Physical violence or any other form of abusive behavior towards fellow residents will not be tolerated within or outside the Institute premises. Anyone found guilty will be liable for strict disciplinary action, including suspension or rustication, depending on the severity of the case. Public display of affection is strictly prohibited.","We hope this handbook provides all necessary information about the Institute. The principal objective of this office is to extend all possible support for the growth and progress of students. The Office of the Dean (Students’ Welfare) is always open to students, and we invite suggestions for improvement. We wish you a very happy, healthy, and comfortable stay on the campus."}	{58822}
