1605	Data Science and Artificial Intelligence	data-science-and-artificial-intelligence	DS	engineering	The department of Data Science and Artificial Intelligence focuses on building expertise in big data analytics, machine learning, and intelligent systems. Students gain exposure to cutting-edge tools, research, and applications that drive innovation in industries ranging from healthcare to finance.	To be a center of excellence in data-driven intelligence, nurturing professionals who can develop ethical, scalable, and impactful AI solutions for global challenges.	To empower students with strong analytical foundations, foster interdisciplinary research, and promote innovations in artificial intelligence and data-driven technologies.	\N
1606	Robotics and Industrial Engineering	robotics-and-industrial-engineering	RA	engineering	The department of Robotics and Industrial Engineering integrates mechanical systems, automation, and production management to develop efficient, smart, and sustainable industrial solutions. The curriculum emphasizes robotics, control systems, and industrial optimization.	To lead advancements in robotics and industrial systems that redefine automation and sustainable manufacturing practices.	To cultivate engineers capable of designing intelligent robotic systems, optimizing industrial processes, and advancing human-robot collaboration.	\N
1609	Architecture and Planning	architecture-and-planning	AP	engineering	The department of Architecture and Planning develops creative professionals capable of designing sustainable spaces and urban environments. The program integrates aesthetics, functionality, and environmental responsibility.	To shape future-ready architects and planners who create innovative, inclusive, and sustainable built environments.	To foster design thinking, promote sustainable urban planning, and integrate modern technology with architectural creativity.	\N
1551	Computer Engineering	computer-engineering	CS	engineering	The department started offering B.Tech. Programme in Computer Engineering in 1987 with initial intake of 30 students and subsequently raised to 210. Department also started B.Tech programme in Information Technology (IT) in 2006 with present intake of 140 students. Department of Computer Engineering is offering a new undergraduate program from the 2023-24 academic session in Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning (AI & ML) with an average intake of 60.	To be a center of excellence in computer science education and research that nurtures innovation, critical thinking, and ethical responsibility. The department envisions producing globally competent professionals and researchers who contribute to technological advancement and societal development through knowledge, creativity, and leadership in the field of computing.	To provide high-quality education by integrating strong theoretical foundations with practical and industry-relevant skills in computer science and engineering. The department aims to foster research, innovation, and entrepreneurship while promoting collaborative learning, professional ethics, and lifelong learning. Through modern infrastructure, experienced faculty, and industry interaction, we strive to prepare students to meet global technological challenges and serve society effectively.	\N
